# Allowed Role-Key Literals

Normal prose should use the moderator role, reviewer, technical-writer role, and platform-engineer role.

| Role key | Meaning |
| --- | --- |
| `mod` | Table rows are allowed because they mirror structured values. |
| `pa` | Table rows are allowed because they mirror structured values. |

**Examples:** If the speaking participant is `mod`, this illustrative line is allowed.

<!-- BEGIN GENERATED:SAMPLE -->
Generated mirrors may contain `tw` and `pe`.
<!-- END GENERATED:SAMPLE -->

```sh
printf '%s\n' 'tw pe pa mod'
```

